{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block header %}
<header class="py-3">
  <div class="container px-5">
    <div class="row gx-5 align-items-center justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-7 col-xxl-6">
        <div class="my-5 text-start">
          <h1 class="display-5 fw-bolder mb-2">What's this all about‚ùì</h1>
          <p class="lead fw-normal mb-4">
            Thanks for asking. Well, this project arose from a personal need
            to stay up to date with what's happening in my country üáøüá≤. I'm
            generally terrible at keeping up with current affairs, so I
            figured I'd put my programming skills to good use and take
            advantage of the recent AI developments to build a tool that
            would help me stay informed. This is the result. I hope you find
            it useful too.
          </p>
          <div class="d-flex flex-column align-items-start flex-md-row justify-content-md-between gap-3" >
            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary px-4" href="/news/">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-newspaper me-2"></i>
                Browse News Digests
            </a>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-dark" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#listen-and-subscribe">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-headphones me-2"></i>
                Listen to Podcast Archive
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xl-5 col-xxl-6 d-none d-xl-block text-center">
        <img
          class="img-fluid rounded-3 my-5"
          src="/img/questions-illustration.svg"
          alt="Zed News"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<section class="section bg-dark py-5">
  <div class="container px-4 px-lg-5">
    <div class="row gx-5">
      <div class="col">
        <div class="text-white">
          <h2 class="fw-bolder text-white mb-3">From Podcast to Daily Digests üì∞</h2>
          <p class="lead text-white">
            After producing <strong>500 podcast episodes</strong> from June 2023 onwards, we've evolved into something even better: <strong>daily text-based news digests</strong>. This transition allows for faster consumption, better searchability, and more efficient news consumption while maintaining the same AI-powered curation and summarization that made the podcast valuable.
          </p>
          <h3 class="fw-bolder text-white mb-3 mt-4">How does this work‚ùî</h3>
          <p class="lead text-white">
            Every weekday, a
            <a
              href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron"
              class="link-warning link-offset-2 link-underline-opacity-25 link-underline-opacity-100-hover"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >cron</a
            >
            job runs
            <a
              href="https://www.cloudflare.com/en-gb/learning/cloud/what-is-the-cloud/"
              class="link-warning link-offset-2 link-underline-opacity-25 link-underline-opacity-100-hover"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >"in the cloud"</a
            >
            to fetch the latest news from multiple Zambian sources.
          </p>
          <p class="lead text-white">
            Each news item is then summarized using a <a href="https://www.deepset.ai/blog/what-is-a-language-model" class="link-warning link-offset-2 link-underline-opacity-25 link-underline-opacity-100-hover" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">language model</a>, and a <a href="https://www.python.org/" class="link-warning link-offset-2 link-underline-opacity-25 link-underline-opacity-100-hover" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Python</a> script compiles everything into a comprehensive daily digest that's organized by themes and importance.
          </p>
          <p class="lead text-white">
            The digest is automatically published to this website, providing you with a clean, scannable summary of the day's most important Zambian news. Links to original sources are organized by publication for easy reference.
          </p>
          <p class="lead text-white">
            All of this happens automatically, without any human intervention - just like our podcast did. It's still a kind of
            <a
              href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rube_Goldberg_machine"
              class="link-warning link-offset-2 link-underline-opacity-25 link-underline-opacity-100-hover"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >Rube Goldberg machine</a
            >, but optimized for the modern way we consume news! üòÑ
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section py-5">
  <div class="container px-4 px-lg-5">
    <div class="row gx-5">
      <div class="col">
        <div>
          <h2 class="fw-bolder mb-3">Key Facts & Features ‚ú®</h2>
          <ul class="fa-ul">
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              Only news items published on the same day are included in each daily digest, ensuring fresh and relevant content.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              No personal opinions are expressed in the digests. News items are presented objectively, without commentary (though the AI may add helpful context!).
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              <strong>Historical Achievement:</strong> We successfully produced <strong>500 automated podcast episodes</strong> from June 2023 onwards, proving the viability of AI-powered news curation. This complete archive remains available for listening.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
               Summaries generated using <a href="https://www.wired.co.uk/article/how-chatgpt-works-large-language-model">LLMs</a> may lack full context, nuance, and may inadvertently introduce biases or inaccuracies due to model limitations. That's why direct links to original articles are provided for fact-checking!
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              <strong>Faster consumption:</strong> Text-based digests can be scanned and read much faster than listening to audio, making it easier to stay informed in our busy world.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              <strong>Searchable content:</strong> Unlike audio, text digests are searchable, making it easy to find specific topics or stories from previous days.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              Links to original news articles are organized by source in collapsible sections, making it easy to explore stories that interest you most.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              This continues to be an experiment in automation and artificial intelligence. The best way to learn is by building and evolving, and that's exactly what we're doing here. We hope you find these daily digests as valuable as our podcast archive.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              The original idea was inspired by
              <a
                href="https://camrobjones.com/hackercast/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >Hackercast</a
              >, which creates AI-generated podcast summaries of
              <a
                href="https://news.ycombinator.com/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >Hacker News</a
              >.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
